Proposed structure for the guided installer (install.cjs rewrite):

```
// Sections:
// 1. Constants: colors, paths, CLAUDE.md snippet, version
// 2. Helpers: ok/skip/fail, ensureDir, copyDirSync, ask(rl, question)
// 3. Detection: detectExisting(targetDir) -> { installed, version, hasData }
// 4. Prompts: promptConfirmInstall, promptClaudeMd, promptSeedCards
// 5. Install logic: installFresh(targetDir, options), installUpgrade(targetDir, options)
// 6. Main: parseArgs, detect, prompt or use defaults, execute

// Key helper for async readline:
function ask(rl, question) {
  return new Promise(resolve => rl.question(question, resolve));
}

// Main flow (async):
async function main() {
  const target = process.argv[2] || process.cwd();
  const nonInteractive = !process.stdin.isTTY || process.argv.includes('--yes');

  printBanner();
  const existing = detectExisting(target);

  if (nonInteractive) {
    // Use all defaults
    if (existing.installed) upgrade(target);
    else freshInstall(target, { claudeMd: true, seed: false });
    return;
  }

  const rl = readline.createInterface({ input: process.stdin, output: process.stdout });
  // ... prompt chain ...
  rl.close();
}
```

**Estimated size:** 200-300 lines. Reuse existing copyDirSync and file operations from current install.cjs. Add readline prompts and detection logic on top.

**CLI interface:**
- node install.cjs [target-path] — interactive guided install
- node install.cjs [target-path] --yes — non-interactive, all defaults
- npx burrow [target-path] — future npm package entry point
